# claim-agent Test Environment

- Use `.venv/bin/pytest` (or `python -m pytest` with `.venv` activated) for running tests.
- Bootstrap runs on agent start via `scripts/bootstrap.sh`; `.venv` has claim-agent + dev deps (pytest, pytest-cov, pytest-xdist, PyJWT).
- Default `addopts` in `pyproject.toml` exclude `llm` and `slow`; override with `-m` as needed.
- Unit tests: `pytest tests/ -v --ignore=tests/integration -m "not slow and not integration and not llm and not e2e"`; add `-n auto` to parallelize (CI unit job uses this).
